The paper deals with computational complexity and approximation algorithms for spin systems, which are typically studied in computer science subfields such as computational complexity (cs.CC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), and statistical learning (cs.SI). The use of random graphs and the Swendsen-Wang algorithm also suggest a connection to random structures and algorithms (cs.RA). However, since the paper focuses on computational complexity and hardness results, cs.CC and cs.DS are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.IT, cs.LG, and cs.SI.
